sandria]]              | caps11 = 7  | goals11 = 0\n| years12             = 2012\u20132013 | clubs12 = [[F.C. Ashdod|Ashdod]]                       | caps12 = 22 | goals12 = 9\n| years13             = 2013\u20132014 | clubs13 = [[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]]            | caps13 = 26 | goals13 = 7\n| years14             = 2014      | clubs14 = [[South China AA|South China]]               | caps14 = 1  | goals14 = 1\n| years15             = 2015      | clubs15 = [[P\u00e9csi MFC]]                                | caps15 = 10 | goals15 = 2\n| years16             = 2015\u20132018 | clubs16 = [[Nea Salamis Famagusta FC|Nea Salamina]]    | caps16 = 92 | goals16 = 30\n| years17             = 2018      | clubs17 = [[FC Arda Kardzhali|Arda Kardzhali]]         | caps17 = 11 | goals17 = 6\n| years18             = 2019      | clubs18 = [[Ermis Aradippou FC|Ermis Aradippou]]       | caps18 = 14 | goals18 = 0\n| years19             = 2019      | clubs19 = [[Podosfairikos Omilos Xylotymbou 2006|PO Xylotymbou]]  | caps19 =    | goals19 = \n| totalcaps           = \n| totalgoals          = \n| nationalyears1      = 2009\u20132011\n| nationalteam1       = [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]]\n| nationalcaps1       = 8\n| nationalgoals1      = 1\n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 18 May 2019\n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n'''Dimitar Ivanov Makriev''' ({{lang-bg|\u0414\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0432}}; born 7 January 1984) is a Bulgarian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\n==Career==\n===Youth career===\nMakriev was raised in [[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]]'s youth teams. In 2002, he signed a contract with Levski's rival [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]].\n\n===Inter Milan===\nFew days after signing Makriev, CSKA Sofia sold him to [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]]. However, he spend the first part of 2002\u201303 season in CSKA, because Italian Federation froze transfers of foreigners from outside the European Union. After that he played on loan for Swiss [[AC Bellinzona]], Polish [[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]] and Swiss [[FC Chiasso]]. In season 2005\u201306,he was a part of French [[Dijon FCO]].\n\n===NK Maribor===\nIn 2006, Makriev signed with [[NK Maribor]]. For two seasons, Makriev earned 48 appearances playing in the [[Slovenian PrvaLiga]], scoring 23 goals.\n\n===F.C. Ashdod===\nIn January 2008, [[F.C. Ashdod|Ashdod]] signed Makriev on a two-and-a-half-year deal. He was given the number 7 shirt. Makriev helped the team save themselves from relegation to the second league in Israel. In 18 games, he scored 11 goals. During the 2008\u201309 season, Makriev scored 11 goals.\n\n===Krylia Sovetov===\nOn 19 May 2011, [[F.C. Ashdod|Ashdod]] accepted an offer for Makriev from [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Krylia Sovetov Samara|Krylia Sovetov Samara]]. On the next day, he passed his medical and signed a three-year deal that will keep him with the club until 2014.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=kc-camapa.ru|script-title=ru:\u041a\u0440\u044b\u043b\u044c\u044f \u0421\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u043f\u0430\u0434\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0441\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0411\u043e\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0438|url=http://kc-camapa.ru/cgi-bin/newsprn.cgi?5591|accessdate=2011-05-20|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\n===Levski Sofia===\nIn late August 2013, Makriev returned to [[Bulgaria]] and signed a one-year contract (with the option for an additional year) with [[Levski Sofia]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=topsport.bg|title=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430 \u0441 \u041b\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0437\u0430 1+1 \u0433., \u043d\u0430\u043f\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f\u0442 \u0449\u0435 \u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0413\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e\u0432|url=http://topsport.ibox.bg/material/id_1115540656|language=Bulgarian|date=2013-08-28}}</ref>\n\n===South China===\nOn 22 August 2014, he moved to Hong Kong team South China AA on a free transfer. However, he had left the club on 10 October 2014 by mutual consent.\n\n===Nea Salamina===\nOn 12 July 2015, Makriev signed a contract with [[Cypriot First Division]] club [[Nea Salamis Famagusta FC|Nea Salamina]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=gol.bg|title=\u0414\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0432 \u0441\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u043c\u0435\u0440\u0438 \u043e\u0442\u0431\u043e\u0440 \u0432 \u041a\u0438\u043f\u044a\u0440|url=http://www.gol.bg/bulgari-v-chujbina/2015-07-12/dimitar-makriev-si-nameri-otbor-v-kipar|date=12 July 2015|language=Bulgarian}}</ref> He appeared in all of Nea Salamina's league matches and scored 19 goals in the [[2015\u201316 Cypriot First Division|2015\u201316 season]], finishing as the league's top scorer alongside [[Fernando Cavenaghi]] and [[Andr\u00e9 Alves]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=cfa.com.cy|title=Makriev 2015\u201316 Statistics|url=http://www.cfa.com.cy/Gr/players/2175542/177472}}</ref>\n\n===Arda Kardzhali===\nOn 30 July 2018, Makriev signed a contract with the newly promoted [[Second Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|Second League]] team [[FC Arda Kardzhali|Arda Kardzhali]].<ref>[http://fcarda.bg/2018/07/30/%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B4%D0%B0-%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%B2%D0%BB%D0%B5%D1%87%D0%B5-%D0%B4%D0%B8%D0%BC%D0%B8%D1%82%D1%8A%D1%80-%D0%BC%D0%B0%D0%BA%D1%80%D0%B8%D0%B5%D0%B2 \u0410\u0420\u0414\u0410 \u0441 \u043d\u043e\u0432 \u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0441\u0444\u0435\u0440 \u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440, \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0432\u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435 \u0414\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0432]</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{Updated|match played on 18 May 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|publisher=soccerway.com|title=Dimitar Makriev Profile|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/demitar-mecrayev/56143/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=90minut.pl|title=Dimitar Makriev Profile|url=http://www.90minut.pl/kariera.php?id=5073}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Club\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Season\n! colspan=\"3\"| League\n! colspan=\"2\"| Domestic Cup{{Efn|Includes both Cup, league cup and Supercup matches, where applicable.}}\n! colspan=\"2\"| Europe{{Efn|Includes [[UEFA Champions League]], [[UEFA Europe League]] and [[UEFA Intertoto Cup]].}}\n! colspan=\"2\"| Total\n|-\n!Division\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]]\n|[[2000\u201301 A Group|2000\u201301]]\n|rowspan=2|[[First Professional Football League|A Group]]\n|1||0||0||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n|[[2001\u201302 A Group|2001\u201302]]\n|1||0||1||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total!!2!!0!!1!!0!!0!!0!!3!!0\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]]\n|[[2002\u201303 A Group|2002\u201303]]\n|[[First Professional Football League|A Group]]\n|0||0||0||0||0||0||0||0\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Inter Milan]]\n|[[2002\u201303 Serie A|2002\u201303]]\n|[[Serie A]]\n|0||0||1||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[AC Bellinzona|Bellinzona]] (loan)\n|2002\u201303\n|[[Swiss Challenge League|Nationalliga B]]\n|14||4||||||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||14||4\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[G\u00f3rnik Zabrze]] (loan)\n|[[2003\u201304 Ekstraklasa|2003\u201304]]\n|[[Ekstraklasa]]\n|22||2||||||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||22||2\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[FC Chiasso|Chiasso]] (loan)\n|[[2004\u201305 Swiss Challenge League|2004\u201305]]\n|[[Swiss Challenge League|Challenge League]]\n|18||5||||||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||18||5\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Dijo